# **AI Platform – Vertical Capability Stack (with Multi-Tenancy)**

Below is a **vertical column-style box diagram**, where each capability domain is represented as a vertical pillar — ideal for showcasing modular components in a platform architecture.

```
+------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------+
|                                                AI PLATFORM – VERTICAL STACK                                                       |
+------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------+
|                                                                                                                                    |
|   +----------------------+     +---------------------------+     +--------------------------+     +--------------------------+     +---------------------------+  |
|   |      USER LAYER      |     | MULTI-TENANCY & PROJECTS  |     |   APPLICATION LAYER      |     |   MLOps + LLMOps LAYER   |     |   DATA & KNOWLEDGE LAYER   |  |
|   |----------------------|     |---------------------------|     |--------------------------|     |--------------------------|     |----------------------------|  |
|   | - Business Users     |     | - Folder & Project-based  |     | - AI/ML Use Cases        |     | - Model Training, Deploy |     | - Data Catalog & Governance|  |
|   | - AI Architects      |     |   Isolation (Dev/QA/Prod) |     | - GenAI Agents, RAG Sys  |     | - Model Registry (MLflow)|     | - Feature Store (Feast)   |  |
|   | - API, Portal, CLI   |     | - Shared Services (IAM)   |     | - Forecasting, NLP, CV   |     | - Prompt Versioning       |     | - Embedding Store (Vector) |  |
|   |                      |     | - Billing & Resource Quota|     | - Real-time / Batch APIs |     | - Feedback Loops          |     | - RAG & Chunk Pipelines   |  |
|   +----------------------+     +---------------------------+     +--------------------------+     +--------------------------+     +----------------------------+  |
|                                                                                                                                    |
|   +-----------------------+    +---------------------------+     +--------------------------+     +--------------------------+     +----------------------------+  |
|   | CI/CD & ARTIFACTS     |    |   INFRASTRUCTURE LAYER    |     | OBSERVABILITY & GUARDRAILS|     | SECURITY & GOVERNANCE     |     | MONITORING & AUTOMATION    |  |
|   |-----------------------|    |---------------------------|     |---------------------------|     |--------------------------|     |----------------------------|  |
|   | - Harness / ArgoCD    |    | - GKE / Unmanaged K8s     |     | - Fiddler / LangSmith     |     | - IAM, KMS, RBAC         |     | - Event-driven Retraining  |  |
|   | - Artifact Registry   |    | - Vertex AI / Cloud Run   |     | - Drift, Bias, Latency     |     | - Compliance (SOC2 etc.) |     | - Scheduler / Functions    |  |
|   | - Promotion Flow      |    | - Multi-cloud Networking  |     | - Guardrails (Bedrock etc.)|     | - API Gateway Policies   |     | - Auto-Parking & Alerts    |  |
|   | - Immutable Storage   |    | - Terraform Templates     |     | - FinOps Dashboards        |     | - SIEM & Threat Detection|     | - Failover & Backup       |  |
|   +-----------------------+    +---------------------------+     +---------------------------+     +--------------------------+     +----------------------------+  |
|                                                                                                                                    |
|                                                +----------------------------+                                                    |
|                                                |   FOUNDATION SERVICES       |                                                    |
|                                                |----------------------------|                                                    |
|                                                | - Networking (VPC, VPNs)   |                                                    |
|                                                | - Storage (Cloud, S3)      |                                                    |
|                                                | - Compute (VMs, GKE Nodes) |                                                    |
|                                                | - Logging, Metrics         |                                                    |
|                                                +----------------------------+                                                    |
|                                                                                                                                    |
+------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------+
```

---

### **Legend**

* Each **vertical box** represents a modular capability pillar.
* **User → Multi-Tenancy → Application → MLOps → Data → CI/CD → Infra → Observability → Security → Monitoring → Foundation** follow top-down hierarchy.
* Multi-tenancy sits early in the stack to signify isolation and governance across shared infrastructure.

---

This vertical structure provides a clear visual representation of **end-to-end AI Platform components** — from users and tenants at the top to foundational services at the bottom — showing how each capability integrates within a unified enterprise AI platform.
